  "chapter": {
    "number": 15,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Gentle Answer Turns Away Wrath"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A gentle answer turns away wrath,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a harsh word stirs up anger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The tongue of the wise commends knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the mouth of the fool spouts folly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The eyes of the LORD are in every place,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "observing the evil and the good.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A soothing tongue is a tree of life,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a perverse tongue crushes the spirit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A fool rejects his father’s discipline,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever heeds correction is prudent.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The house of the righteous has great treasure,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the income of the wicked is trouble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The lips of the wise spread knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but not so the hearts of fools.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is detestable to the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the prayer of the upright is His delight.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD detests the way of the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He loves those who pursue righteousness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Discipline is harsh for him who leaves the path;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he who hates correction will die.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sheol and Abaddon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4230
          },
          {
            "text": "lie open before the LORD—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "how much more the hearts of men!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A mocker does not love to be reproved,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will he consult the wise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A joyful heart makes a cheerful countenance,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but sorrow of the heart crushes the spirit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A discerning heart seeks knowledge,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the mouth of a fool feeds on folly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the days of the oppressed are bad,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a cheerful heart has a continual feast.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better a little with the fear of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than great treasure with turmoil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better a dish of vegetables where there is love",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than a fattened ox with hatred.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A hot-tempered man stirs up strife,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who is slow to anger calms dispute.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The way of the slacker is like a hedge of thorns,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the path of the upright is a highway.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wise son brings joy to his father,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a foolish man despises his mother.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Folly is joy to one who lacks judgment,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a man of understanding walks a straight path.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Plans fail for lack of counsel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but with many advisers they succeed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man takes joy in a fitting reply—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and how good is a timely word!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The path of life leads upward for the wise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that he may avoid going down to Sheol.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD tears down the house of the proud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He protects the boundaries of the widow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD detests the thoughts of the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the words of the pure are pleasant to Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who is greedy for unjust gain brings trouble on his household,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but he who hates bribes will live.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The heart of the righteous ponders how to answer,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the mouth of the wicked blurts out evil.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD is far from the wicked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but He hears the prayer of the righteous.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The light of the eyes cheers the heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and good news nourishes the bones.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who listens to life-giving reproof",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will dwell among the wise.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who ignores discipline despises himself,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but whoever heeds correction gains understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The fear of the LORD is the instruction of wisdom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and humility comes before honor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
